  "prompt": "What are the chances that Barack Obama will again become the president of the United States of America in the election of 2016?",
  "response": "Barack Obama served as the 44th President of the United States for two terms, from January 20, 2009, to January 20, 2017. According to the 22nd Amendment to the U.S. Constitution, a person can be elected to the presidency **only twice**. This means that Barack Obama is constitutionally ineligible to run for the presidency again in any future elections, including the 2016 election.\n\nIn the 2016 United States presidential election, Barack Obama did not run for a third term. Instead, the election featured candidates such as Hillary Clinton for the Democratic Party and Donald Trump for the Republican Party. Donald Trump won the 2016 election and served as the 45th President from January 20, 2017, to January 20, 2021.\n\nIf you have any more questions about U.S. presidential elections or related topics, feel free to ask!",
